Like already implemented with CI-3281 for locations of Rheinmetall AG and Rheinmetall Immobilien, the same replacement procedure is needed for all the listed locations above, too.

At the moment at least for Rheinmetall Waffe and Munition (RMW) "&" are part of the export files and cause error in the SAP system behind.
The rest of the locations listed above needs to be checked, too and if not yet implemented, the replacing procedure is also needed to be implemented.
With CI-3281 this was implemented with the following function replacement for Rheinmetall AG:
before replacement
function writeElement(b,e,a,c)\{var d ="";if(e){d = e}if(d.length> c&& c!=0)\{d= d.substr(0,c -1)}output.writeEndFieldMaxLength(Array(a+1).join(" ")+"<"+b+">"+ d+"</"+b+">",0,fileName)}

after replacement
function escapeCharacter(d)\{var b ={"&":"&amp;", " <":"&lt;", " >":"&gt;", ' " ' :"&quot;","'":"&#39;","/":"&#x2F;"};var c=""+d ;var a="";if(d)\{a=c.replace(/[&<>"'\/]/g,function(e){return b[e]})}return a}function writeElement(b,f,a,d)\{var e= "";if(f){e =f}if(e.length> d&& d!=0)\{e= e.substr(0,d)}var c=e.substring(e.length-5,e.length);if(c.search("&")!=-1)\{e=e.substring(0,(e.length-5+c.search("&")))}output.writeEndFieldMaxLength(Array(a+1).join(" ")+"<"+b+">"+ e+"</"+b+">",0,fileName)}

Maybe the same can be used for the locations listed above.

 

Thanks,
Nicole

